
1. The Republic of Zambia takes its name from the Zambezi river which flows along the 
border between Zambia and Zimbabwe.
2. Zambia is a landlocked country and its eight neighbouring countries are the Democratic 
Republic of Congo (DRC) to the north, Tanzania, Malawi and Mozambique to the east, Zimbabwe, 
Botswana and Namibia to the south and Angola to the west.
3. The official language of Zambia is Engish, however, there are over 72 languages spoken in the country.
4. Zambia is home to one of the worldâ€™s biggest waterfalls: Victoria Falls.
5. Zambia has the largest man-made lake in the world, Lake Kariba.
